headline: A Fresh Look at AMD’s Valuation as Intel Foundry Talks and AI Partnerships Fuel Investor Interest
summary: Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) is back in the spotlight as reports confirm the company is in early talks to diversify its chip manufacturing through a potential partnership with Intel’s foundry business. In addition, AMD is expanding its AI reach by collaborating with IBM to deploy Instinct MI300X GPUs on IBM Cloud for large-scale model training, and is also deepening ties with Cohere for broader enterprise and government AI offerings.
